    Title:
      "Visier Appoints Lexy Martin Principal of Research and Customer Value",
    Content:
      '<h2><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Former Human Resources Analyst and Researcher Brings Four Decades of Experience in Research, Value Analysis, and Change Management to Visier</span></i></h2>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">VANCOUVER, BC and SAN JOSE, CA – June 14, 2016 – </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Visier</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, the leader in Workforce Intelligence, today announced that Lexy Martin has joined the company as Principal, Research and Customer Value. Martin brings more than 40 years of thought leadership experience in introducing workplace initiatives and emerging technologies with a background as a researcher, management consultant, and application development manager. In her new role at Visier, Martin will work closely with Visier customers to support them in their HR transformation.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">“Having tracked workforce analytics adoption for over fifteen years, I’ve been a big fan of Visier since its inception. When I decided to return to the workforce, I could not imagine a better place to apply my passion and skills in research, value analysis, and change management,” said Martin. “After just a few days on the job, I’m overjoyed. The people are welcoming, talented, and passionate about all things workforce intelligence.”</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">A sought-after thought leader and speaker, few researchers in the field of HR technology can match the experience that Martin has accumulated during her career in introducing emerging technologies. Prior to joining Visier, Martin was Vice President, Research and Analytics at Sierra-Cedar where she assisted organizations worldwide in defining strategies to implement enterprise applications by providing visioning, strategy development, process innovation, value analysis, and business case development. She also developed major change management and organizational learning programs to accompany the introduction of new initiatives and technologies to promote their success. Martin was also the lead author and director of the Sierra-Cedar Human Resources Systems Survey, the longest running and most acclaimed Human Resources technology survey.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">“Lexy’s reputation for helping companies leverage technology as a catalyst for change is legendary,” said John </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Schwarz</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, Founder and CEO, Viser. “With Lexy’s appointment, Visier gains an experienced and proven advisor who will help our customers implement effective Workforce Intelligence solutions that improve managerial decision-making, streamline business processes, collaboration and employee empowerment.”</span>\n<h4><b>About Visier</b></h4>\nVisier’s purpose is to help people see the truth and create a better future—now.\n\nVisier was founded to focus on what matters to business people: answering the right questions, even the ones a person might not know to ask. Questions that shape business strategy, provide the impetus for taking action, and drive better business results.\n\nVisier delivers fast, clear people insight by using all the available people data—regardless of source. With best-practice expertise built-in, decision-makers can confidently take action. Thanks to our amazing customers, Visier is the market leader in Workforce Analytics with 5,000 customers in 75 countries around the world.\n\nFor more information, visit http://www.visier.com.\n\n<b>Media Contact:\n</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Joseph Martorano\n</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">415.321.1865\n</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">visier(at)sparkpr(dot)com</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;',
