    id: 26085,
    Title:
      "Visier Benchmarks Offer Fortune 2000 Unmatched New Insights into Workforce Performance",
    Content:
      '<span style="font-weight: 400;">SAN JOSE, Calif. and VANCOUVER, October 9, 2017 – Visier, developer of </span><a href="https://www.visier.com/solutions/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Visier Workforce Intelligence</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, the </span><a href="https://www.visier.com/hr-leadership/visier-people-strategy-platform/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">leading people strategy platform</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, today announced Visier Benchmarks, a new capability that will allow customers to easily compare data about their own workforce to confidentially sourced benchmark data from Visier customers.</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">“Every organization wants to compare their results to accurate, complete, and timely data on their peers and competitors,” says Dave Weisbeck, Chief Strategy Officer, Visier. “Yet–until now– the benchmarks available to employers have been based on self-reported surveys that are compiled once a year, meaning they are incomplete, inaccurate, and out of date. With Visier Benchmarks, companies are able to access timely and relevant comparison data.”</span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Included as part of the Visier Workforce Intelligence solution, Visier Benchmarks will use data that is sourced directly from Visier customers. Visier Benchmarks complements government-published measures such as those from the U.S. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission and U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics—also available directly within Visier—by adding even more relevant context and timeliness.</span>\n<h3><b>Designed for the Speed of Business Decisions</b></h3>\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Visier Benchmarks will be available on demand and include workforce metrics the business cares most about, such as resignation and promotion rates, with a level of detail that allows actionable insights where it matters. For instance, users will be able to see benchmarks by performance groups, tenure ranges, manager status, age, diversity, region, and industry. Because Visier Benchmark data is generated automatically from integrating data across Visier customers, users will have real-time access to up-to-date benchmarks.</span>\n<h3><b>Data from Peers</b></h3>\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Visier Benchmarks data comes from large organizations—ranging from thousands to hundreds of thousands of employees across a span of industries—making them more relevant comparison points for large employers than government data, which can come from organizations with as few as 50 employees.</span>\n<h3><b>Unbiased Information</b></h3>\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Visier Benchmarks includes data for all employees—instead of a self-selected sample of respondents that can lead to biased results. Because workforce information is collected and standardized directly from systems of record, Visier Benchmarks are more reliable than surveys that rely on subjective self-reports.</span>\n\nFind data-driven HR insights and tips at <a href="https://www.visier.com/clarity" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.visier.com/clarity</a>\n\nFollow Visier on Twitter <a href="https://twitter.com/visier" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@Visier</a>\n\nVisier and Visier logo are trademarks of Visier, Inc. All other brand and product names and logos are the trademarks of their respective holders.\n\n<strong>About Visier</strong>\n\nVisier’s purpose is to help people see the truth and create a better future—now.\n\nVisier was founded to focus on what matters to business people: answering the right questions, even the ones a person might not know to ask. Questions that shape business strategy, provide the impetus for taking action, and drive better business results.\n\nVisier delivers fast, clear people insight by using all the available people data—regardless of source. With best-practice expertise built-in, decision-makers can confidently take action. Thanks to our amazing customers, Visier is the market leader in Workforce Analytics with 5,000 customers in 75 countries around the world.\n\nFor more information, visit http://www.visier.com.\n\n<strong>Media Contact:</strong>\nJulie Galla\nvisier(at)sparkpr(dot)com',
