    Title:
      "Visier Launches ‘Women in Leadership Speaker Series’ Across Multiple Cities to Foster a Community for Women Leaders of Tomorrow",
    Content:
      '<h2><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Featuring </span></i><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">inspirational career stories shared by top women executives, the Visier Women in Leadership Speaker Series will provide  powerful career advice including strategies to address the “Manager Divide”</span></i></h2>\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>SAN JOSE, CA and VANCOUVER, BC</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">  – August 21, 2018 – To inspire women leaders of tomorrow, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Visier</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, the recognized leader in people analytics and planning, is launching a multi-city Women in Leadership Speaker Series, kicking off with events in Charlotte, Toronto, and Houston. The luncheon events will feature women executive leaders who will share </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">inspirational career stories as well as lessons learned on their path to success. </span>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">A leading voice on the issue of gender equity, Visier is launching this speaker series to jump-start industry-level conversations and share smart strategies to address the continuing inequalities in pay and management roles uncovered in the </span><a href="https://hello.visier.com/gender-equity-report-visier-insights/"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Visier Insights: Gender Equity</span></i></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">report. A key report finding – the</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Manager Divide</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> – clearly linked an underrepresentation of women in manager positions at key points in their careers to a widening of the gender wage gap. The report also concluded that eliminating the Manager Divide would cut the gender wage gap by nearly one third. </span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">"This speaker series is the next step in our mission to build community around women in leadership and address the issues surrounding gender pay equity and the manager divide that we uncovered in our ground-breaking Visier Insights Gender Equity report," said Josie Sutcliffe, Vice President of Marketing, Visier. "By sharing stories of exceptional female leaders, we hope to inspire other women leaders to take their careers to the next level."</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Initial dates and locations for Visier’s Women in Leadership Speaker Series lunches are as follows: </span>\n\n<b>Charlotte, NC - October 4th, 2018</b>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Speakers:</span>\n<ul>\n \t<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Maryann Bruce, Paradigm for Parity</span></li>\n \t<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kathy Cook, VP Global Processes &amp; Analytics, Ingersoll Rand</span></li>\n \t<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jocelyn Caldwell, Vice President, HR Strategy and Planning - Workforce Analytics &amp; Planning, TIAA</span></li>\n</ul>\n<b>Toronto, ON - October 18, 2018</b>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Speakers:</span>\n<ul>\n \t<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Lynn Roger, Global Head of Employee Experience &amp; Workplace Transformation, BMO</span></li>\n \t<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Emmanuela Heyninck, Commissioner, Ontario Pay Equity Commission</span></li>\n \t<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Simone Reitzes, Vice President, Global Pension &amp; Benefits, Scotiabank</span></li>\n</ul>\n<b>Houston, TX - November 14, 2018</b>\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Speakers:</span>\n<ul>\n \t<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sue Ortenstone, Senior Vice President &amp; Chief Human Resources Officer, CenterPoint Energy</span></li>\n \t<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stephanie Speights, Vice President, Talent Management &amp; Chief Learning Officer, Children’s Health of Texas</span></li>\n</ul>\n<b>About Visier</b>\n\nVisier’s purpose is to help people see the truth and create a better future—now.\n\nVisier was founded to focus on what matters to business people: answering the right questions, even the ones a person might not know to ask. Questions that shape business strategy, provide the impetus for taking action, and drive better business results.\n\nVisier delivers fast, clear people insight by using all the available people data—regardless of source. With best-practice expertise built-in, decision-makers can confidently take action. Thanks to our amazing customers, Visier is the market leader in Workforce Analytics with 5,000 customers in 75 countries around the world.\n\nFor more information, visit http://www.visier.com.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Contact:</b><b>\n</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Julie Galla</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">\n</span><a href="mailto:visier@sparkpr.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">visier@sparkpr.com</span></a>',
    Excerpt: "",
    Date: "2018-08-21",
    Permalink:
      "https://www.visier.com/press-release/visier-launches-women-in-leadership-speaker-series-for-women-leaders/",
    Slug: "visier-launches-women-in-leadership-speaker-series-for-women-leaders",
    _yoast_wpseo_metadesc:
      "Featuring inspirational career stories shared by top women executives, the Visier Women in Leadership Speaker Series will provide powerful career advice.",
